OL,3,CFIFA U-turns on water bottle ban at
OL,4,CWorld Cup after backlash
OL,6,FIn May, academics at World Weather
OL,7,FAttribution (WWA) expressed concern
OL,8,Fabout the impact of extreme heat on
OL,9,Fplayer and fan welfare, with
OL,10,Fsupporters said to be especially
OL,11,Fvulnerable.
OL,13,FWWA expects nine of the 104 World Cup
OL,14,Fmatches to be played at a Wet Bulb
OL,15,FGlobe Temperature (WBGT) above 26
OL,16,Fdegrees.
OL,18,FWBGT is an index that considers how
OL,19,Feffectively the body can cool itself,
OL,20,Fnot just the air temperature.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
